<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="cool-adj">cool <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kuːl/    美 /kuːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>凉爽的；凉快的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The cool air feels good on a hot summer day.
炎炎夏日，凉爽的空气让人感到很舒服。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>冷静的；沉着的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>as cool as a cucumber</strong>
泰然自若；极为冷静</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>More importantly, you can <strong>stay cool</strong> under pressure.
更重要的是，面对压力时你能保持冷静。</p><footer>2008 安徽</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>冷漠的；冷淡的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has been cool towards me ever since we had a quarrel.
自从我们争吵以后他对我一直很冷淡。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>极好的；绝妙的；酷的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her guy’s really cool.
她男朋友真帅。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>没问题；好：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Can you come at eight tomorrow morning? 
你能明天早上8点过来吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— <strong>Cool</strong>. / <strong>That’s cool</strong>.
没问题。</p></div></div>